From: Florian Westphal <fw@strlen.de>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2024 12:27:15 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] netfilter: tproxy: bail out if IP has been disabled on the
 device
Git-commit: 21a673bddc8fd4873c370caf9ae70ffc6d47e8d3
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc2
References: CVE-2024-36270 bsc#1226798

syzbot reports:
general protection fault, probably for non-canonical address 0xdffffc0000000003: 0000 [#1] PREEMPT SMP KASAN PTI
KASAN: null-ptr-deref in range [0x0000000000000018-0x000000000000001f]
[..]
Rip: 0010:nf_tproxy_laddr4+0xb7/0x340 net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_tproxy_ipv4.c:62
Call Trace:
 nft_tproxy_eval_v4 net/netfilter/nft_tproxy.c:56 [inline]
 nft_tproxy_eval+0xa9a/0x1a00 net/netfilter/nft_tproxy.c:168

__in_dev_get_rcu() can return NULL, so check for this.

Reported-and-tested-by: syzbot+b94a6818504ea90d7661@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Fixes: cc6eb4338569 ("tproxy: use the interface primary IP address as a default value for --on-ip")
Signed-off-by: Florian Westphal <fw@strlen.de>
Signed-off-by: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_tproxy_ipv4.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_tproxy_ipv4.c
+++ b/net/ipv4/netfilter/nf_tproxy_ipv4.c
@@ -58,6 +58,8 @@ __be32 nf_tproxy_laddr4(struct sk_buff *
 
 	laddr = 0;
 	indev = __in_dev_get_rcu(skb->dev);
+	if (!indev)
+		return daddr;
 
 	in_dev_for_each_ifa_rcu(ifa, indev) {
 		if (ifa->ifa_flags & IFA_F_SECONDARY)
